"Normally, I wouldn't let you off with just that level of
injury... but, I'll make an exception and let you go this
time."

"You're an unlucky guy, honestly, I feel a bit of sympathy
for you. Now get on home quickly. I won't be so lenient next
time."
"Ugh... damn it... damn it... Makoto... Makoto... uhh..."

"That's right... my smartphone should be safe... the
police... I should call the police..."

After being beaten by the henchmen and driven out from the
underground, I decided to rely on the police to somehow
rescue Makoto. A few minutes after making the call, two
officers arrived at my location.

I dragged my aching body and led the officers to the
building I had come from earlier. However, the door was
locked, so we had no choice but to look through the small
windows on either side to see the staircase inside.

But the officer who peered inside said that he couldn't see
any staircase. In a panic, I also looked through the small
window, and indeed, the staircase had disappeared. I became
confused and tried to forcibly pry the door open.

The officers hurriedly stopped me from trying to break the
door and, to my dismay, took me outside the factory. They
lectured me about not making prank calls to the police and
were about to leave.

I desperately explained that the staircase was hidden, but
the officers wouldn't listen and I couldn't keep them from
leaving. I was completely ignored by the police and had no
more options left.

In the end, unable to do anything, I went home. After
returning, I cried out of frustration and called Makoto over
and over, but Makoto never answered my calls.
